Innings break We will take a break and return in 40 minutes time for the run chase.

Dwaine Pretorius has told the TV broadcaster that Australia probably got 10-15 runs more than they should have but the South Africans are pleased with their bowling performance. Australia had three players reach 40 but none reached 50. Rabada took four and Pretorius bowled very well to take 3 for 32. Chris Lynn tells the TV broadcaster they might be 50 short but they will back the bowlers to do the job. Too many starts from the batsmen.

Four wickets for Rabada and Australia ar bowled out with nine balls remaining.
